description: Moderation queue, review workflow, and policy-driven automation
globs: backend/app/services/moderation*, backend/app/services/notification*, backend/app/workers/moderation*, backend/app/api/**/moderation*, backend/app/api/**/policies*
---

Moderation workflow features (see PRD):
- Moderation queue: list of videos/streams pending or requiring human review; priority and filters.
- Policy-driven automation: auto-flag, auto-reject, or escalate based on policy rules and AI output.
- Human review: optional escalation to human review; configurable per policy; audit trail.
- Alerts and notifications: real-time alerts for violations, SLA or backlog thresholds; notify via configured channels (email, webhook, in-app).

Rules:
- Moderation results and queue items must be first-class entities in the data model (docs/DB_SCHEMA.md); link videos/streams to moderation results and policies.
- Policy evaluation and routing logic must live in services, not in routes.
- Escalation and auto-action logic must be configurable (rules or thresholds); avoid hardcoded IDs.
- Alert and notification logic should run in workers or event-driven paths; support idempotency and audit logging.
- Auto-action (e.g. auto-reject) must respect business rules and policy config; log actions for audit.
- Duplicate or batch handling: use video_id, stream_id, or job_id for idempotency; link to canonical record where applicable.

Do not:
- Put moderation decision or queue update logic only in HTTP handlers; support async pipeline (Celery, webhooks) for scale.
- Assume single-tenant; scope queue and policies by tenant/organization where applicable.
- Trigger automation without idempotency and audit trail where state changes are critical.
